(I still find it funny the Red Sox ended up winning the World Series that year) 👀

Well this #tbt will complete my #RedTour journey from 2013. What an incredible experience, where I met life long friends, and learned so much. This was 10 years ago today. Getting to close out my time on the tour with two dates at @gillettestadium - for a kid from Holland, Massachusetts this meant the world. Very thankful 🙏🏻 … My career has brought a world of ups and downs. Some days I feel like crying, screaming, jumping for joy, on top of the world, or just plain confused, but I will always love the gift God has given me. I love to sing my songs for people. I love to write. I love music. I can not wait to share the Americana music I’ve been writing and recording lately. #singersongwriter #music

@dariusrucker announced his new album last week! Comes out October 6th! Head to his page and Pre-save it- had the pleasure of writing “Sara” with Darius, Ed Sheeran and Kyle Rife.
It’s not every day you get to go to the legendary Casa Bonita. IYKYK #casabonita #denver

@dariusrucker album is out and it’s so good! Had the honor of writing Sara with Darius, Ed Sheeran, and Kyle Rife. Can’t forget @joerubel with the Demo after we wrote it. Was such a fun day and night. It’ll go down on the lifelong memories list for sure. Very grateful.

I posted this Friday morning before I found out a friend had passed away the night before. This photo was from our trip to England where we wrote “Sara.”On that trip I met a new friend, Mark Cummins. Having only known him 4-5 years, we shared quite a few memorable experiences together. He also had a great way of making you feel like you’ve known each other forever. He once convinced me to play in a golf tournament, the night before the tournament. I had only been playing a few weeks and never played a full round before. Truthfully, I was terrified to do it, and I was terrible. However, mark had a way of just getting you out of your head and feeling comfortable with yourself. So… I was still terrible that day, but we had a blast. Haha - and funny enough, our team ended up winning! He was one of the nicest guys I’ve met. I’m proud to have called him a friend. I’ll miss you mark.
This could be my first photo 💩… “just a little bit of life…”
